# PROJECT RULES

## General
- This project is a Dockerized Node.js webhook service.
- No UI routes are expected unless explicitly defined.
- Prefer simplicity over abstraction.

## Git
- Use conventional commits when possible:
  feat: add feature
  fix: bug fix
  chore: maintenance
- Never commit secrets (.env, tokens, keys).
- Always ensure builds are reproducible from GitHub.

## Docker
- Images are built via GitHub Actions only.
- Local builds are allowed for debugging only.
- Do not rely on local node_modules inside containers.
- Always use explicit image tags in production deployments.

## CI/CD
- GitHub Actions is the single source of truth for builds.
- Every push to main triggers:
  1. Docker build
  2. Push to GHCR
  3. SSH deployment to server

## Deployment
- Server uses docker-compose only.
- No manual container configuration on production.
- Deployment must always be idempotent.

## Secrets
- All secrets must be stored in GitHub Secrets.
- Never hardcode credentials in source code.

## Code style
- Keep services modular (controllers / services / router separation).
- Avoid over-engineering.
- Prefer explicit code over magic behavior.

## Debugging
- Use docker logs for runtime issues.
- Use GitHub Actions logs for build issues.
- Use SSH only for deployment or emergency recovery.


## Versioning
- Prefer tagging releases using git SHA or semver.
- Avoid relying on `latest` in critical environments.